HP ENVY Desktop Computer, Intel Core i7-9700, 16GB RAM, 1TB Hard Drive, 512 GB SSD, Windows 10 (TE01-0020, Black)
Review: My unit received was actually damaged from a forklift prong or similar bashing though the box and thus defective/inoperable, which should have never been delivered from the giant gash through box. But as a now 40 year techie I did get a chance to see what was inside, both motherboard, case design, components. These are F grade and you cannot re-purpose, reuse or replace. Hard drive was a thin ultra-cheap Seagate (never recommended, unethical to give this to people as a main hard drive!) Power unit was like 200-250 power range - just enough to power the ultra-low end build. DVD drive paper thin F grade. Wifi-bluetooth, USB hubs everything F Grade. Designed as cheap as possible. HP (and DELL) are both fill-in-blank today. If anything breaks (including the paper thin DVD drive), it cannot be replaced on basically either due to motherboard, psu and actual case design. Nor can it really be used with any rationality in another case. I imagine the cpu, ssd and ram are in fact in the only elements that are good and are going to be third-party, intel and samsung based parts. So why would someone spend the money when you are better off buying a better case, psu, media drive and motherboard and then your cpu/ram by a long long mile? Extremely unethical PC build designed to fill-in-the-blank computer shoppers. Shocking. What happened to these companies? Grade F- And I am serious F-. I hope this review really helps someone out and saves them imminent disaster or loss. People and companies should play fair, act honorably and nice to each other. HP no longer trusted with desktops- never again.,I am not a gamer so I do not use for online gaming. I do use this for my home office and after 3 laptops have an office space dedicated to work time. I paired this with a 34” lg ultra wide monitor. All I can say is Awesome. The ssd drive allows this to boot up more like an I pad than a pc. It’s always ready to go I can run pandora and word and excel and surf the Internet or retrieve bank statements all at the same time and this baby doesn’t slow or show me the circle of waiting. I highly highly recommend,Doesn't run hot like my 2012 HP Win 7 pc used to. Had a hard time locating the on button as it needs to protrude out more. When I tried to depress it at first nothing happened. Couldn't find the DVD player for days as everything is so concealed. Very sleek design. This is not a gaming pc as that's not what I was looking for. Bought extra powerful pc so won't have to upgrade later, hopefully. Very happy with it.,The HP Envy is exactly what I thought it should be. Very fast with calculations and applying the various programs that I installed. The inside is cramped, so if anyone wants to add memory (as I did) or to try to change the HDD to an SSD, it will be difficult.,The computer seemed ideal for one of my Building Automation Display computers. But, I had a few problems. In my application, the machine is required to run 24 hours a day on a UPS. This computer initially shut down every few days and had to be manually restarted. HP support came online and reinstalled the Windows 10 OS from scratch and this fixed that problem. In this application, I have to have two identical displays connected, running the same video. First I tried to do this by connecting one display in by the regular VGA port and the second (a touchscreen) via one of the USB ports. This words, BUT, every day or so, the "duplicate the same screen on both VGA displays" feature quits working for one or the other displays. I also tried just running the TWO displays from the ONE VGA port. Unfortunately, the VGA display port shuts down if you try to run two displays from the port.,This has plenty of power and memory for my Quickbooks software, plus I do lots of personal stuff on the internet, like shopping, email etc. I do not play any games so I have no idea if it's suited for that. It was not advertised as a gaming computer.,This product will not support any upgrades needed for graphics or gaming. The power supply is only 180w with proprietary wiring. Unable to add graphics card as power supply cannot support. HP technical support non existant, do not respond to questions on their website. I did find an obscure third party document saying that they can be upgraded which provided a part number for the power supply. Not available in the US, need to buy from Hong Kong. THis is not acceptable, HP need to support their customers, in my case Ex customer.,I think it was a refurbished computer because it came with a wireless mouse that doesn't work and there are no instructions as to how to put the battery in if it needs one, also the instructions refer to a wired mouse. The 8 pages of instructions that did come with it refer to page 11? the keyboard doesn't work properly and won't let me connect to the internet.

Review: I purchased one of these NUCs to run retro video games in a HyperSpin arcade cabinet and it handles everything I’ve thrown at it like a champ.,Works like it should. Don't let the numbers foold you. Even though the RAM and HD are high, the pc will lag even when not under stress. You neee atleast 8GB of RAM, because the pc will be using around 2 on idle. It does get the job done at the end of the day. It handles everyday task like docs, web surding, and youtube very well. There is a small buzzing noise which is quite noticible if you are close to it. All in all, if I wanted a gaming pc, I'd get something bigger like how it should be. I'd use this for small space and productive situations.,After 1st use the startup is slowing down,Tossed the (slow) HDD and 4gb RAM. Replaced with 1TB SSD and 32GB RAM. No complaints. I love the small form factor.,This is good product for watching youtube and browsing webs and decent games. You will need to add nvme ssd to prevent hypertension, this 1tb hdd is really slow.,Works as expected. Nice little machine.

Title: Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 8GB DDR4 RAM, 512GB SSD + 2TB HDD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 64GB DDR4 RAM, 1TB SSD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Review: This thing rocks. I purchased it to replace a tower that was approximately ten years old. It was quite easy to set up. A few tips: (1) the video port is hdmi, so if you have an older monitor, you may need to buy a converter, (2) it doesn’t have a dvd drive, so if you have software on a dvd that you want to load, you will need an external dvd drive, (3) it doesn’t have a lot of USB ports, and you will need some of them for your keyboard and mouse, so you may want to buy a hub, particularly if you will also be using an external dvd drive.,Sooo glad I got this. Just replaced my big desktop box, and this is faster, more storage, and about 1/50th the volume. Super easy setup... QSG not included because it's not needed.,I’m using this as my proxmox homelab host and it’s incredible. Such amazing power and ram packed into a small box. Complete powerhouse. I run a dozen VMs and 6 containers and only using half the ram (32/64).,After years of using computers this is the first time I enjoyed the speed of a computer may be because i bought 64Gb RAM and 1 TB SSD but its amazing I would write some of the things that can be improved although I love it as it is but these improvements can make it even greater.,I specced an expensive NUC config to build out a streaming rig (separate from the gaming box) and was suffering a bit from sticker shock, when I found this unit. Same specs are at least $100 cheaper (and most of the time, more cheap) than non-amazon-prime sellers. That it was shipped via Prime was just cherry on top.,I know, it's corny, but after years of lugging around massive towers, this tiny PC does all the same work in a flash! Photoshop loads in seconds, batch reduces files in minutes, video rendering is about 4x realtime (14 minutes to render an hour-long HD video), and takes up minimal space on my desktop! I picked up a 12TB external drive for data storage, an external DVD drive for importing legacy video, and a docking station to give me plenty of additional ports.,I am a software developer so I need raw disk and CPU power (not video editing). I ordered the 64 GB model on 10/22/20 with a 10 day delivery estimate. They shipped FedEx overnight and it arrived on 10/24/20. That was a nice touch.,This product worked well for a month, it’s really fast and tiny. It started having issues like in 35 days, the monitors shut down suddenly and computer was still on. I then tried starting it by removing the power cord and pressing power button 2 times and then putting power cord back on and it started few times. Now it does not start at all. I don’t recommend buying this product- My Toshiba laptop which is 8.5 years old still works which is windows 7. It’s better to buy a Dell pc rather than to buy from a seller who might put substandard parts into this machine. I will try to repair it as I got warranty still on it and if that does not work then I will try to get refund. I am really upset with this purchase.

Title: Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 64GB DDR4 RAM, 512GB SSD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Review: I bought a NUC 10 with the goal of starting a simple home lab, this machine will be running VMs. Other users in the answers indicated they received a NUC with an NVMe SSD which would be ideal for a simple virtualization server.,Disappointed with the sellers equipment selection. Of course the series 10i7 chip is top notch, but found the two 8gB memories to be of the cheapest, slowest quality and mismatched by brand and speed. While it included a 500GB SSD, it did not make clear if it was sata or NVMe. What shipped was a low quality no-name SATA only available on eBay. As a result I will be replacing both the SATA and RAM with better quality items. Very miffed they would sell a top quality NUC and processor with junk components. I didn't expect the best ram and SSD, but these fall so far below as to be worthless.,The Intel NUC computer was shipped quickly and setup easily. While testing the computer I noticed that every component performed well except for the Solid State Drive (SSD). The benchmark software gave it a rating of 3925 which was equivalent to the worst SSD performance I’ve seen in a decade. I checked the drive for errors and found none. The drive is just UNBELIEVABLY SLOW. It makes the computer perform poorly for many tasks (including booting).,My first NUC was an i5 with 8GB memory and 256GB SSD. My daughter has that one now (not sure how old).,This little box screams power especially coming from a 9 year old Toshiba laptop. Even though I upgraded it to a SSD and doubled the RAM, it is just not able to keep up, but this NUC 10, is like getting warp drive. I bought the 16gig of Ram and 512gig drive model and it turns on in seconds. Love it so far!,I've always had a PC connected to TV as an HTPC, browser, and occasional gamer. And along the way, I've had a lot of NUCs. The NUCs have something of a history in my house, sometimes being too noisy, too slow, too hot, or not good enough video. This one seems to have really nailed it, and for this price you get a solid system with Win10 Pro and some expansion room. I'm running everything 30' away with bluetooth keyboard+mouse. it is driving a 4k TV with no problem using a long-reach HDMI-over-fiber cable and an AV receiver in the middle.,This is the second Intel Nuc Mini Pc that I purchased and had to be returned because both were defective. I won't purchase this brand again.,I really wanted to like this NUC. I think I just got a bad one. Mine uad a problem with the USB port which was inconvenient because I took it with me to use out of town so it was real frustrating not being able to use it when I needed it.

Title: Intel NUC 8 Mainstream Kit (NUC8i5BEK) - Core i5, Short, Add't Components Needed
Review: The problem with i7 nucs is that they are small, but not silent. This generation does not fix it. For all the usual tasks, like watching youtube, doing office work or really light gaming, it is quite and stays around 40 C. But if you were hoping to use its i7 to its full potential, be prepared for the nuc to hit 85 degrees with irritating fan noise.,I had the NUC7i5BNH but sold it due to the constant fan noise or coil whine which was really annoying. I recently bought the NUC8i5BEK and I can state that it is very quiet compared to the previous (7th gen.) model. Intel finally listened to consumers and put a better cooling system into the NUC for the 8th gen. CPUs. Also, the Core i5-8259U is a much stronger CPU than the previous i5-7260U.,Works out of the box with Proxmox VE and Ubuntu 18.04. On-board NIC not currently compatible with ESXi 6.7.,This review is for the BOXNUC8i5BEH1, the "tall" i5 "kit" that does not include RAM or HDD. (Note that i3, i5, and i7 reviews are unhelpfully combined here, unless you know how to filter the reviews.)

Title: Intel NUC NUC8I7HVK Mini PC, Intel QuadCore i7-8809G Upto 4.2GHz, 16GB DDR4, 256GB NVMe SSD, AMD Radeon RX Vega M GH, WiFi, Thunderbolt 3, 4k Support, Windows 10 Pro (16GB Ram + 256GB SSD)
Review: bought this for my son after watching many videos showing how amazing this mini pc is. after trying to set it up, we realized how much of a real rip off it is. We bought the 32gb and 512 ssd model which comes with both already installed. My son is a gamer so he wanted to play fortnite/ rainbow six siege. both wouldn't launch saying the graphics card did not reach the requirement or it needed to be upgraded. We went to the intel driver site and that was an even bigger pain to install. Over all, very very bad product, all of the other good reviews are fake. Trust me on this, do not buy the product.,i order the 32g ram / 512g ssd combo,The only reason I'm giving this 3 stars is I do not like false "bait & switch" offerings since the internal SSD was not what was advertised as a 2TB Samsung 970 NVMe. I installed a 2nd 2TB Samsung 970 NVMe and when I opened the NUC8I7HVK up, what I found in the other slot was a 2TB Intel 660p which I've pictured. Although the Intel is slower than the Samsung in benchmark transfer speed & therefore costs less, it probably will not be noticeable. Its just the fact that some of the lower star reviews also mentioned that they didn't get the stated brand of components makes this seller on my "buyer beware" list. I even posted a question to the seller if they could install a 2nd 2TB Samsung Evo NVMe but they couldn't as it had already been shipped. I'm glad they didn't as I probably would have gotten two Intel 660p or maybe even less. Other than that, the rest of the components, OS and processor were correct, it does run fast as expected. I use for multitasking (no gaming) and its hooked up to the new LG Ultrawide 49WL95C-W monitor. The small form factor was perfect must since the monitor takes up most of the desk.,This thing is so lame. I don't know why it is but it is! I purchased 3 of these from the same people and that in and of itself was a mistake.The sound almost never works. There is ALWAYS work to do if I want sound. Video playing is ridiculous. I get more error messages while running video (mostly basic mp4). I have and alwas have had much difficulty with mp4s, both locally as well as streaming like youtube. Intel dropped the ball on this mini PC because I have so many problems and I have the troubles on both of thes HVK models. The HNK one seems to be working fine for my wife because she hasn't complained. Both HVK models are using large tv screens as their one and only monitor. Both TVs are newer 4k models. I thought it might be that but I ran a regular monitor and no change besides, I would think Intel has long solved TV's, HDR etc.. My arrangement is common nowadays. The seller could not have cared any less about my problems and never helped me one iotta and never followed up with me...NEVER!! I would NOT buy a NUC again and will not give this merchant my return business no matter what and that is what I recommnend for other buyers... unless you are really good and don't mind a bit of trouble and need no assistance (support) from the seller. If you can make it past those glaring shortcomings then break out the cc and go for it!,Received my NUC and works great, but! one issue that will not go away no matter what I try and that is the driver for the tps65988 USB power port will not update, I have used Intels update site but the driver never corrects the problem. I've search the web for answers but no one seems to have corrective actions on this issue. So I have to give this a low rating on the system not the seller.,It's awesome! I don't use this for gaming, so this might not be the review for you. I use this for work as a laptop alternative as it's size is very portable. The power supply is nearly as big as the PC and is difficult to find a spare. Intel is giving me the run around. Apparently it's not a very common request as a spare part. Otherwise it is incredibly fast for every task I use it for and the connectivity is awesome.,UPDATE: DON't BUY THIS! After returning I bought this from another seller and had problems with it the whole time until now, a year and a half later. Now it's died completely. POS For this amount of money I expected a top quality product that would last many years!,Here's what you need to know about this machine before you buy it:

Review: I bought a NUC 10 with the goal of starting a simple home lab, this machine will be running VMs. Other users in the answers indicated they received a NUC with an NVMe SSD which would be ideal for a simple virtualization server.,Disappointed with the sellers equipment selection. Of course the series 10i7 chip is top notch, but found the two 8gB memories to be of the cheapest, slowest quality and mismatched by brand and speed. While it included a 500GB SSD, it did not make clear if it was sata or NVMe. What shipped was a low quality no-name SATA only available on eBay. As a result I will be replacing both the SATA and RAM with better quality items. Very miffed they would sell a top quality NUC and processor with junk components. I didn't expect the best ram and SSD, but these fall so far below as to be worthless.,The Intel NUC computer was shipped quickly and setup easily. While testing the computer I noticed that every component performed well except for the Solid State Drive (SSD). The benchmark software gave it a rating of 3925 which was equivalent to the worst SSD performance I’ve seen in a decade. I checked the drive for errors and found none. The drive is just UNBELIEVABLY SLOW. It makes the computer perform poorly for many tasks (including booting).,My first NUC was an i5 with 8GB memory and 256GB SSD. My daughter has that one now (not sure how old).,This little box screams power especially coming from a 9 year old Toshiba laptop. Even though I upgraded it to a SSD and doubled the RAM, it is just not able to keep up, but this NUC 10, is like getting warp drive. I bought the 16gig of Ram and 512gig drive model and it turns on in seconds. Love it so far!,I've always had a PC connected to TV as an HTPC, browser, and occasional gamer. And along the way, I've had a lot of NUCs. The NUCs have something of a history in my house, sometimes being too noisy, too slow, too hot, or not good enough video. This one seems to have really nailed it, and for this price you get a solid system with Win10 Pro and some expansion room. I'm running everything 30' away with bluetooth keyboard+mouse. it is driving a 4k TV with no problem using a long-reach HDMI-over-fiber cable and an AV receiver in the middle.,This is the second Intel Nuc Mini Pc that I purchased and had to be returned because both were defective. I won't purchase this brand again.,I really wanted to like this NUC. I think I just got a bad one. Mine uad a problem with the USB port which was inconvenient because I took it with me to use out of town so it was real frustrating not being able to use it when I needed it.
